  "chunk_index": 22,
  "summary": "Bobby meets with Moira Nicholson, who reveals that she is the wife of Dr. Nicholson. Terrified and trembling, Moira confesses her belief that her husband intends to murder her. She explains that she has experienced several \"accidents\" that she believes were intentional, such as being nearly run over by a vehicle and finding medications mixed up in bottles. Moira claims her husband's motive is his infatuation with Sylvia Bashington-French. She suspects Dr. Nicholson is arranging for Sylvia's husband, Henry Baxton-French, to be brought to Granchester Sanatorium as a patient. Moira believes a man named Jasper is manipulating Henry—who takes morphine—and his brother Roger to facilitate this move to the sanatorium, a place she describes as sinister where patients get worse rather than better.\n\nMoira expresses doubt about Sylvia's true nature, wondering if the woman is merely acting. She also notes that Jasper is influencing Roger to help bring Henry to Grange. When Bobby asks if she knows Allen Castles, Moira admits she knew him before her marriage and that he visited her about a month ago without her providing his location. She has not told Castles about her fears or her unhappy marriage. Finally, Moira states that her husband is a very strange man who is extremely jealous of Bobby, viewing Moira as his property.",
